Bache Securities Inc, 80 pct owned byPrudential Bache Securities Inc, said it acquired its thirdToronto Stock Exchange seat for 301,000 Canadian dlrs.    The company said the price was the highest yet paid for anexchange seat. A Toronto Stock Exchange spokesman said anexchange seat last sold for 195,000 dlrs in March, which wasacquired by &lt;Toronto Dominion Bank>.    Bache Securities said it needed a third exchange seat aspart of an extensive plan to provide an enhanced level ofservice to clients. The seat will be used to further build itsprofessional trading area, the investment dealer said. Reuter&#3;